        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-11-13T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-11-13T07:00:00-05:00" n="490" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d490">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11–1347: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tihwa</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Paxton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tihwa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-11-13T18:00:00+06:00">November 13, 1947—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 14—11:48 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>69. Mme. Hate-Wan, Tihwa zone commissioner, yesterday brought Hereld Estson,
                    recently with other Kazaks at Chenghua fighting, to Consulate. He confirmed
                    previous reports (refmytel to Nanking 401, repeated Dept 62, October 24) of Red
                    Army assistance in recent expulsion by Ili forces of Osman’s men from zone
                    capital, saying that entire campaign was under political direction of
                    Dipshatoff, Acting Soviet Consul at Chenghua, and that expedition had entered
                    from USSR under military leadership (see Tihwa telegram to Embassy 159, April
                        21<note n="49" xml:id="d490fn1">See airgram No. A–85, April 30, from the
                        Ambassador in China, <ref target="#pg_553">p. 553</ref>.</note>) of Generals
                    Polinoff and Madjoroff.</p>
                <p>Much the same story was told by two White Russian “old believers” fleeing from
                    same region who called earlier yesterday.</p>
                <p>Sent Embassy, as 431, repeated Dept as 69.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Paxton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
